text: Merijärvi is a municipality in Northern Ostrobothnia, Finland. As of 31 December 2023, 1,055 people lived there. Neighbouring municipalities are Alavieska, Kalajoki, Oulainen, Pyhäjoki and Ylivieska. Most people speak Finnish. Merijärvi was founded in 1866. == Other websites == * Municipality of Merijärvi – Official website Category:1866 establishments in Finland Category:Municipalities of North Ostrobothnia
